Patch summary:
Derive the gfxstream host blob page size from the host page size instead of a
hardcoded 4096. On 16K-page hosts (Apple Silicon under Asahi) the udmabuf-backed
host-visible blob path aligns its shared-memory size to kPageSizeforBlob before
calling UDMABUF_CREATE; a 4096 value under-aligns the region (the kernel requires
the system page size, 16384) and the import/map fails. kPageMaskForBlob is the
matching host-VA alignment mask used by the blob mapping guard. All uses are
runtime (size alignment, pointer-alignment checks, comparisons), so switching
from constexpr 4096 to getpagesize() is safe; <unistd.h> is already included.

diff --git a/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp b/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp
--- a/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp
+++ b/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp
@@ -171,8 +171,12 @@
     VK_KHR_EXTERNAL_SEMAPHORE_CAPABILITIES_EXTENSION_NAME,
 };

-static constexpr uint64_t kPageSizeforBlob = 4096;
-static constexpr uint64_t kPageMaskForBlob = ~(0xfff);
+// ika: derive the blob page size from the host page size so the SystemBlob/
+// udmabuf host-visible path aligns correctly on 16K-page hosts (Apple Silicon
+// under Asahi). A hardcoded 4096 under-aligns udmabuf imports and blob sizes,
+// causing UDMABUF_CREATE / mapping failures on 16K pages.
+static const uint64_t kPageSizeforBlob = static_cast<uint64_t>(getpagesize());
+static const uint64_t kPageMaskForBlob = ~(static_cast<uint64_t>(getpagesize()) - 1);

 static std::atomic<uint64_t> sNextHostBlobId{1};
 static std::atomic<uint64_t> sUniqueShmemId = 0;
